<section id="introduction" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
<p>Counting integer solutions is a central idea in algebra, number theory, and combinatorics. Here the word <strong>positive</strong> matters: each variable must be at least <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?1">, not merely non-negative.</p>
<p>We will count the solutions in four complementary ways. The mathematics supplies the proof; Python provides an independent verification.</p>
<div class="article-info">
<p><strong>Difficulty:</strong> Intermediate<br> <strong>Prerequisites:</strong> Basic algebra, inequalities, and elementary counting<br> <strong>Estimated reading time:</strong> 8 minutes</p>
</div>
</section>
<section id="problem" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="problem">Problem</h2>
<p>Find the number of positive integer solutions of</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0Ax+2y+3z=15,%0A"></p>
<p>where <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?x,y,z%5Cin%5Cmathbb%20Z%5E+">. The answer will be</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cboxed%7B12%7D.%0A"></p>
</section>
<section id="method-1-fix-one-variable-and-count" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="method-1-fix-one-variable-and-count">Method 1: Fix One Variable and Count</h2>
<p>Solving for <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?x"> gives</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0Ax=15-2y-3z.%0A"></p>
<p>Since <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?x%5Cgeq1">, we have <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?2y+3z%5Cleq14">. Because <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?y%5Cgeq1">, this gives <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?2+3z%5Cleq14">, so <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?z%5Cleq4">. Thus <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?z=1,2,3,4">.</p>
<p>For each fixed <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?z">, count the positive values of <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?y"> for which <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?x=15-2y-3z"> stays positive.</p>
