<section id="method-2-convert-positive-integers-to-non-negative-integers" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="method-2-convert-positive-integers-to-non-negative-integers">Method 2: Convert Positive Integers to Non-negative Integers</h2>
<p>Write</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0Ax=a+1,%5Cqquad%20y=b+1,%5Cqquad%20z=c+1,%0A"></p>
<p>where <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?a,b,c%5Cgeq0">. Substitution gives</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A(a+1)+2(b+1)+3(c+1)=15,%0A"></p>
<p>and hence</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0Aa+2b+3c=9.%0A"></p>
<p>For fixed <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c">, this becomes <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?a+2b=9-3c">. An equation <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?a+2b=N">, with <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?a,b%5Cgeq0">, has <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cleft%5Clfloor%20N/2%5Cright%5Crfloor+1"> solutions because <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?b"> ranges from <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?0"> to <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%5Cleft%5Clfloor%20N/2%5Cright%5Crfloor">.</p>
