<section id="method-3-direct-floor-function-formula" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="method-3-direct-floor-function-formula">Method 3: Direct Floor-Function Formula</h2>
<p>For fixed positive integer <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?z">, positivity of <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?x"> implies</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A15-2y-3z%5Cgeq1,%0A"></p>
<p>so</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0Ay%5Cleq%5Cfrac%7B14-3z%7D%7B2%7D.%0A"></p>
<p>The number of positive integer values of <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?y"> is therefore</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cleft%5Clfloor%5Cfrac%7B14-3z%7D%7B2%7D%5Cright%5Crfloor.%0A"></p>
<p>Since <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?z=1,2,3,4">,</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0AN=%5Csum_%7Bz=1%7D%5E%7B4%7D%5Cleft%5Clfloor%5Cfrac%7B14-3z%7D%7B2%7D%5Cright%5Crfloor.%0A"></p>
<p>Evaluating the sum,</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0AN=%0A%5Cleft%5Clfloor%5Cfrac%7B11%7D%7B2%7D%5Cright%5Crfloor+%0A%5Cleft%5Clfloor%5Cfrac%7B8%7D%7B2%7D%5Cright%5Crfloor+%0A%5Cleft%5Clfloor%5Cfrac%7B5%7D%7B2%7D%5Cright%5Crfloor+%0A%5Cleft%5Clfloor%5Cfrac%7B2%7D%7B2%7D%5Cright%5Crfloor%0A=5+4+2+1=%5Cboxed%7B12%7D.%0A"></p>
</section>
<section id="method-4-generating-functions" class="level2">
<h2 class="anchored" data-anchor-id="method-4-generating-functions">Method 4: Generating Functions</h2>
<p>The positive values of <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?x">, <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?2y">, and <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?3z"> are encoded respectively by</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cfrac%7Bt%7D%7B1-t%7D,%5Cqquad%0A%5Cfrac%7Bt%5E2%7D%7B1-t%5E2%7D,%5Cqquad%0A%5Cfrac%7Bt%5E3%7D%7B1-t%5E3%7D.%0A"></p>
<p>Their product is</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0AG(t)=%0A%5Cleft(%5Cfrac%7Bt%7D%7B1-t%7D%5Cright)%0A%5Cleft(%5Cfrac%7Bt%5E2%7D%7B1-t%5E2%7D%5Cright)%0A%5Cleft(%5Cfrac%7Bt%5E3%7D%7B1-t%5E3%7D%5Cright)%0A=%5Cfrac%7Bt%5E6%7D%7B(1-t)(1-t%5E2)(1-t%5E3)%7D.%0A"></p>
<p>Choosing <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?t%5Ex">, <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?t%5E%7B2y%7D">, and <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?t%5E%7B3z%7D"> from the three factors produces</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0At%5Ex%5Ccdot%20t%5E%7B2y%7D%5Ccdot%20t%5E%7B3z%7D=t%5E%7Bx+2y+3z%7D.%0A"></p>
<p>Thus every positive solution contributes exactly one <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?t%5E%7B15%7D"> term, so the answer is</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Bt%5E%7B15%7D%5DG(t)%0A=%5Bt%5E9%5D%5Cfrac%7B1%7D%7B(1-t)(1-t%5E2)(1-t%5E3)%7D.%0A"></p>
<p>That coefficient is <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?12">, in agreement with the direct counts.</p>
</section>
